    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 26,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "But Job answered and said,",
    "hash": "f65acd19d797e07425b81014a3e7e1e1b687f6c6f777056186616c73f26df942"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.26.2",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 26,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "How hast thou helped {him that is} without power? {how} savest thou the arm {that hath} no strength?",
    "hash": "21ce296b2024e03ce821aba10a745116e8f74ec1752d1dbeb302744171d07e39"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.26.3",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 26,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "How hast thou counselled {him that hath} no wisdom? and {how} hast thou plentifully declared the thing as it is?",
    "hash": "1ac922499c5ab9f65609e407d16ff8daad4fb190889625571402c11427fc3d4f"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.26.4",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 26,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "To whom hast thou uttered words? and whose spirit came from thee?",
    "hash": "ab21af23a620c947fe2bf86fa30d066a048c651f072780b1bde0df3e4f6a4c0f"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.26.5",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 26,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Dead {things} are formed from under the waters, and the inhabitants thereof. {and the...: or, with the inhabitants}",
    "hash": "ec99da14649814d87dba1d9644bd2b714b260d95b779d01ad0bf1112123190b3"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.26.6",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 26,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Hell {is} naked before him, and destruction hath no covering.",
    "hash": "a0da68c1e4d7b3f38be04a78baac8d0cbdc7de3a65e08bfb1a34041bd70b328c"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.26.7",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 26,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "He stretcheth out the north over the empty place, {and} hangeth the earth upon nothing.",
    "hash": "d4ad6d30f859d7fc9b4ca60cbce7eb8447a66f69c0c61e1078b5fefe443df06c"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.26.8",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 26,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "He bindeth up the waters in his thick clouds; and the cloud is not rent under them.",
    "hash": "0aa4e1fa29deacaa2061e0831562339ac472e1400b80ac1cc722108022aa62fa"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.26.9",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 26,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "He holdeth back the face of his throne, {and} spreadeth his cloud upon it.",
    "hash": "b913caf8859d505f23938b88add892eb2629bc3bf8ec7b9c87544606ca2bcce7"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.26.10",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 26,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "He hath compassed the waters with bounds, until the day and night come to an end. {until...: Heb. until the end of light with darkness}",
    "hash": "e8c6771c31c52ce3de3e014e43282fc75581ec0ee6649e6cf1e9eb015713e5ab"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.26.11",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 26,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "The pillars of heaven tremble and are astonished at his reproof.",
    "hash": "b5a39bf2fe5426280487c616cc600c31e23ca28a52f5b723d60dffd614d12b03"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.26.12",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 26,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "He divideth the sea with his power, and by his understanding he smiteth through the proud. {the proud: Heb. pride}",
    "hash": "59de476dbf6f346796e9d3a971fb07fd691057579865dcd11babddef946c9f2e"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.26.13",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 26,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "By his spirit he hath garnished the heavens; his hand hath formed the crooked serpent.",
    "hash": "c6137035f07dc148ec54e60d7f07f340a7683a1c34f2fbcd777e8927be7e1e36"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.26.14",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 26,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Lo, these {are} parts of his ways: but how little a portion is heard of him? but the thunder of his power who can understand?",
    "hash": "bc364295cefb02af5e92fdaf6136c4cd419334c703cd58fc3667869a9c90536a"
  }
]